C o m m e n t: The original description of this anophthalmous species is based a unique male from 
<collectingRegion id="D927F816603C5A6372146A7FCF6646DE" box="[377,576,882,904]" country="Ecuador" name="Pichincha" pageId="1" pageNumber="1120">Pichincha province</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7F724B05603C5A63713F6A7FCFF946DE" author="ASSING V" box="[594,735,882,904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1120" pagination="1541 - 1547" refId="ref5517" refString="ASSING V. (2013): Two new species and a new record of Dolicaonina from Ecuador (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 45 (2): 1541 - 1547." type="journal article" year="2013">ASSING 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The above female is externally identical to the 
<typeStatus id="C4588856603C5A63723D6A82CC8D46F3" box="[336,427,911,933]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1120">holotype</typeStatus>
, suggesting that both specimens are conspecific. It was collected in a cloud forest by sifting the litter layer (BRACHAT pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
